---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | AuthLayer"
  description="AuthLayer publishes plain-English guides to authentication, identity, and cybersecurity for developers and security engineers."
>
  <section class="about-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <span class="tag">About</span>
        <h1>What is AuthLayer?</h1>
      </header>

      <div class="about-body">
        <p>
          <strong>AuthLayer</strong> is a content site dedicated to making authentication and
          cybersecurity accessible to developers, architects, and security engineers.
        </p>

        <p>
          Identity and authentication are the front door to every system — yet the specs are dense,
          the terminology is inconsistent, and the pitfalls are subtle. AuthLayer exists to close
          that gap with clear, technically accurate writing.
        </p>

        <h2>What we cover</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>OAuth 2.0 & OIDC</strong> — authorization flows, grant types, token handling</li>
          <li><strong>JWT</strong> — structure, signing algorithms, validation, common vulnerabilities</li>
          <li><strong>Multi-factor authentication</strong> — TOTP, FIDO2, WebAuthn, push notifications</li>
          <li><strong>Passkeys</strong> — the passwordless future powered by FIDO2/WebAuthn</li>
          <li><strong>Zero Trust</strong> — identity-centric security architecture</li>
          <li><strong>API Security</strong> — securing REST and GraphQL APIs</li>
          <li><strong>Identity Providers</strong> — Okta, Auth0, AWS Cognito, Azure AD and more</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who writes this?</h2>
        <p>
          Articles are written by practitioners with hands-on experience in identity platforms,
          cloud infrastructure, and application security. We focus on accuracy, depth, and
          practical implementation over surface-level tutorials.
        </p>

        <h2>Found an error?</h2>
        <p>
          Security content needs to be accurate. If you spot a mistake, outdated information,
          or a misleading claim — please reach out. Corrections are always welcome.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page { padding: 3rem 0 5rem; }

  .page-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .page-header .tag { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-header h1 { font-size: 2rem; color: #fff; margin-top: 0.5rem; }

  .about-body { max-width: 700px; }

  .about-body p { color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }

  .about-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about-body ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-body li {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .about-body li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .about-body strong { color: var(--text); }
</style>
